The problem of packing disks without overlap is a classic problem in computational geometry, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algorithms to approximate the problem and the study of its complexity suggest that it could also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of minimizing the distance between the leftmost and rightmost points of any disk in the packing could also be seen as a game theory problem (cs.GT) or a computational complexity problem (cs.CC).
